  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>In RepairQ, managers can download export files from RepairQ as Excel-formatted spreadsheets. These Excel exports are useful for maintaining records and quickly viewing details about your business.</p><p>Export data will be limited by any filters set for that list. It is also important to remember that large system exports can cause your RepairQ instance to slow down significantly.\u00a0Whenever possible, use a smaller, focused export in favor of a large one. Exports that are considered too large usually span multiple locations and cover many catalog items.</p><h3 id=\"PurchaseOrders:Exporting-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933377786/RepairQ+Data+Import+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933377786\" data-linked-resource-version=\"18\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RepairQ Data Import Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932427416/Purchase+Order+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932427416\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Purchase Order Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1931411625/Purchase+Orders+Importing+and+Uploading\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1931411625\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Purchase Orders: Importing and Uploading</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932394561/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"PurchaseOrders:Exporting-ExportingPurchaseOrders\">Exporting Purchase Orders</h2><p /><p>1. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Inventory</strong> \u2192 <strong>View</strong> <strong>Purchase</strong> <strong>Orders</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"566\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932394561/PO%20Import%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Purchase Order List page, use the filters to locate the PO you would like to export. Once you find the PO,\u00a0click the <strong>Options Button (\u22ee)</strong> under the Actions column. From the list of options, click <strong>View</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932394561/PO%20Import%2010.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932394561/PO%20Import%2011.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: Alternatively, you can click anywhere on the row of a Reconciled PO to view it.</p><p /><p>3. When viewing the Purchase Order, click the <strong>Export</strong> <strong>button</strong> along the top row. The file will download in your browser.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932394561/PO%20Import%2012.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>4. When viewing the export file, the information will include the following:</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932394561/PO%20Import%2013.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Supplier</strong> - The company that supplied the item.</p></li><li><p><strong>Location</strong> - The location this item was ordered for.</p></li><li><p><strong>Supplier SKU</strong> - Any supplier SKUs that have been linked to this item.</p></li><li><p><strong>UPC</strong> - The UPC assigned to the catalog item.</p></li><li><p><strong>Internal</strong> <strong>SKU</strong> - The SKU assigned to the catalog item.</p></li><li><p><strong>Description</strong> - The catalog name for the item.</p></li><li><p><strong>Ordered</strong> <strong>Qty</strong> - The amount that was ordered/requested on the PO.</p></li><li><p><strong>Rejected</strong> <strong>Qty</strong> - If this was an internal transfer, the quantity that was rejected by the supplying location.</p></li><li><p><strong>Shipped</strong> <strong>Qty</strong> - If this was an internal transfer, the quantity that was shipped from the supplying location.</p></li><li><p><strong>Received</strong> <strong>Qty</strong> - This is the amount received on the Purchase Order. This only applies to items that are partially received or reconciled.</p></li><li><p><strong>Unit</strong> <strong>Price</strong> - This is the cost to purchase from the supplier, i.e., the PO item cost.</p></li><li><p><strong>PO</strong> - The Purchase Order ID</p></li><li><p><strong>Order</strong> <strong>Date</strong> - The date/time of the order.</p></li><li><p><strong>Notes</strong> - Any notes included on the PO line item.</p></li></ul><p /><p /><p>START 1.19.X</p>",
